{"title_page": "Live for You (album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Live for You\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[Rachael Lampa]]\n| cover      = RachaelLampaLiveForYou.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = August 8, 2000\n| recorded   = 2000\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary Christian Music|CCM]], [[Pop (music)|pop]]\n| length     = 45:44\n| label      = [[Word Records|Word]]\n| producer   = [[Brown Bannister]], [[Brent Bourgeois]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Kaleidoscope (Rachael Lampa album)|Kaleidoscope]]\n| next_year  = 2002\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{AllMusic|class=album|id=mw0000085132| accessdate= September 30, 2018}}}}</ref>\n| rev2      = \n| rev2Score = \n}}\n'''''Live for You''''' is the debut album of [[contemporary Christian music|Christian]] [[pop (music)|pop]] singer [[Rachael Lampa]], released in 2000 on [[Word Records]]. It debuted at No. 2 on [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] magazine's \"Top Heatseeker's Album\" chart{{citation needed lead|date=September 2018}} and No. 6 on SoundScan's Top Current Contemporary Christian album chart.{{citation needed lead|date=September 2018}}\n\n== Track listing ==\n\nLyrics and music by the following songwriters.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" |} \n|----- bgcolor=\"#ebf5ff\"\n! # !! width=\"310\" | Title !! | Writer(s) !! | Length \n|- \n| 1. || \"Day of Freedom\" || [[Brent Bourgeois]], [[Chris Eaton (UK musician)|Chris Eaton]], [[Cindy Morgan (singer)|Cindy Morgan]] || 4:37\n|- \n| 2. || \"Live For You\" || Eaton, [[Chris Rodriguez]] || 3:57\n|- \n| 3. || \"Always Be My Home\" || Eaton || 5:26\n|- \n| 4. || \"God Loves You\" || Bourgeois, [[Jill Phillips]] || 3:12\n|- \n| 5. || \"Blessed\" || Morgan, [[Ginny Owens]] || 4:04\n|- \n| 6. || \"You Lift Me Up\" || Eaton, Morgan || 3:38\n|- \n| 7. || \"Shaken\" || [[Anointed|Da'dra Crawford-Greathouse]], Morgan, [[David Mullen]] || 3:12\n|- \n| 8. || \"Free\" || Bourgeois, Morgan || 4:37\n|- \n| 9. || \"Hide Me\" || Bourgeois, Morgan || 3:59\n|- \n| 10. || \"Secret Place\" || Bourgeois, Rodriguez ||  4:29\n|- \n| 11. || \"My Father's Heart\" || Eaton || 4:33\n|}\n\nRemixes of the following are included on ''[[Blur (Rachael Lampa album)|Blur]]''\n* \"Day of Freedom (Mirage Mix)\"\n* \"Live for You (Marbella Mad Motion Mix)\"\n* \"Blessed (Epiphonic Mix)\"\n* \"Free (Holla Back Mix)\"\n\nA limited-edition version was release with three behind-the-scenes segments, and a tour of Lampa's high school. This version was packaged with a slipcase and exclusive fold-out poster.{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n==Singles==\n{{unreferenced section|date=September 2018}}\n*\"Blessed\" No. 1 AC (2 wks)\n*\"Shaken\" No. 1 CHR (3 wks)\n*\"God Loves You\" No. 1 AC (3 wks); No. 9 AC Song of 2000\n*\"Live For You\" No. 1 AC & CHR; No. 5 AC & No. 7 CHR Song of 2000\n*\"My Father's Heart\" No. 2 INSPO\n*\"You Lift Me Up\" No. 4\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Rachael Lampa}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Live for You (Album)}}\n[[Category:2000 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Word Records albums]]\n[[Category:Rachael Lampa albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Live for You\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[Rachael Lampa]]\n| cover      = RachaelLampaLiveForYou.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = August 8, 2000\n| recorded   = 2000\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary Christian Music|CCM]], [[Pop (music)|pop]]\n| length     = 45:44\n| label      = [[Word Records|Word]]\n| producer   = [[Brown Bannister]], [[Brent Bourgeois]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Kaleidoscope (Rachael Lampa album)|Kaleidoscope]]\n| next_year  = 2002\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{AllMusic|class=album|id=mw0000085132| accessdate= September 30, 2018}}}}</ref>\n| rev2      = \n| rev2Score = \n}}\n'''''Live for You''''' is the debut