{"title_page": "Carolina Cortesi", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n[[File:Carolina Cortesi by Gerolamo Prepiani.jpg|thumb|Carolina Cortesi c.1819]]\n'''Carolina Cortesi''' (''floruit'' 1819\u20131821) was an Italian [[contralto]] who in her brief career sang in the premieres of several operas of the early 19th century. Most notably, she created the roles of Eduardo in Rossini's ''[[Eduardo e Cristina]]'' and Edemondo in Meyerbeer's ''[[Emma di Resburgo]]''.<ref name=\"Origo\" /><ref name=\"Naxos\" /><ref name=\"Stend\" /><ref name=\"Johnson\" /><ref name=\"STI\" /><ref name=\"Letel\" /><ref name=\"AA\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs =\n\n<ref name=\"Origo\">Origo, Iris (2000). [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=X0klDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT26 ''The Last Attachment: The Story of Byron and Teresa Guiccioli''], p. 13. Pushkin Press. {{ISBN|1782272844}} (originally published in 1949 by C. Scribner's Sons)</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Naxos\">Jernigan, Charles (2017). [https://www.naxos.com/mainsite/blurbs_reviews.asp?item_code=8.660466-67&catNum=660466&filetype=About%20this%20Recording&language=English Liner Notes: ''Eduardo e Cristina'']. [[Naxos Records]]. Retrieved 3 December 2019.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Stend\">[[Stendhal]] (1824). [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=UkVAAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA208 ''Memoirs of Rossini''], p. 208. T. Hookham</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Johnson\">Johnson, Victoria; Fulcher, Jane F.; Ertman, Thomas (2007). [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=e6ocp3t0VSwC&pg=PA99 ''Opera and Society in Italy and France from Monteverdi to Bourdieu''], p. 99. Cambridge University Press. {{ISBN|1139464051}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"STI\">[[s.n.]] (1821). [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=xxVYAAAAcAAJ&pg=RA2-PP2&lpg=RA2-PP2#v=onepage&q&f=false \"Teatro all Pergola\"]. ''Scelto Teatro Inedito'', Vol. 16, p. 244</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Letel\">Letellier, Robert Ignatius (2006). [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=YofJZHIH2kYC&pg=PA62 ''The Operas of Giacomo Meyerbeer''], pp. 62